This article is a transcript of a press briefing on Air Force One en route to New York. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan discusses the President's message on lowering the costs of college education and the need for greater transparency in higher education. He also talks about the proposed rating system for colleges and the role of Congress in implementing it. Duncan addresses concerns about tying financial aid to college performance and discusses the importance of providing incentives to institutions that are doing a good job. He emphasizes the need for college to be accessible and affordable for all students, regardless of their background. The article also briefly touches on other topics such as aid to Egypt and the situation in Syria.